
=== Build Gear ===


1. Introduction

   Build Gear is a lightweight embedded build system for experienced GNU/Linux
   users and developers. The primary focus of this build system is to keep it
   simple, which is reflected in a straightforward command line build interface,
   and easy to maintain build files. The secondary focus is build performance
   and build integrity. Build Gear is easy to use and well suited for rapid product 
   and prototype development.


2. Installation

   See INSTALL file for details on how to build and install Build Gear.


3. Documentation

   Visit http://www.buildgear-project.org/doc for documentation.


